HEADWORD: Disdiaclast
<hw>Dis*di"a*clast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <grk>diakla^n</grk> to break in twain;
<grk>dia`</grk> through + <grk>kla^n</grk> to break.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>One of the dark particles forming the doubly
refracting disks of muscle fibers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disdiapason</ent>⟦br⟧
